 |f(x)-f(y)| = \left| \frac{(y+1) \sin(x^3) - (x+1)\sin(y^3)}{(x+1)(y+1)}\right| \\ \leq \left| \frac{y\sin(x+1) - x\sin(y+1)}{(x+1)(y+1)}\right| + \left|\frac{\sin(x+1)-\sin(y+1)}{(x+1)(y+1)} \right| \\ \leq \frac{2 \max(x,y)}{(x+1)(y+1)}+\frac{2}{(x+1)(y+1)} \\ < \frac{2}{\min(x,y)}+\frac{2}{(x+1)(y+1)} \\ < 2\frac{1}{k}+2\frac{1}{k} \\ < 4(\epsilon/4) = \epsilon. 
